#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 25"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:0.5"
msgid "25. Cīvaradānasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on giving robe-cloth"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.59, pts-cs-bu-pc25.1, pts-vp-en.2.282, ms2V_558
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarissā visikhāya piṇḍāya carati."
msgstr "At that time a certain monk was walking for almsfood along a street in Sāvatthī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.3"
msgid "Aññatarāpi bhikkhunī tassā visikhāya piṇḍāya carati."
msgstr "as was a certain nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And that monk said to that nun,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.5"
msgid "“gaccha, bhagini, amukasmiṃ okāse bhikkhā diyyatī”ti."
msgstr "“Go to such and such a place, Sister, and you will get alms,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.6"
msgid "Sāpi kho evamāha—“gacchāyya, amukasmiṃ okāse bhikkhā diyyatī”ti."
msgstr "and she said the same to him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.7"
msgid "Te abhiṇhadassanena sandiṭṭhā ahesuṃ."
msgstr "And because they met frequently, they became friends."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.8"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena saṃghassa cīvaraṃ bhājīyati."
msgstr "Just then robe-cloth belonging to the Order was being distributed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho sā bhikkhunī ovādaṃ gantvā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then, after going to the instruction, that nun approached that monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.10"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and stood to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.11"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho taṃ bhikkhuniṃ so bhikkhu etadavoca—“"
msgstr "That monk then said to her,"

#. VAR: cīvarapaṭivīso → … paṭiviṃso (bj) | … paṭiviso (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.12"
msgid "ayaṃ me, bhagini, cīvarapaṭivīso; sādiyissasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Sister, will you accept my share of the robe-cloth?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.13"
msgid "“Āmāyya, dubbalacīvarāmhī”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, Venerable, my robes are worn.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_559
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.14"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu tassā bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ adāsi."
msgstr "And he gave his robe-cloth to that nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.15"
msgid "Sopi kho bhikkhu dubbalacīvaro hoti."
msgstr "As a consequence his robes too became worn."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.16"
msgid "Bhikkhū taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Other monks said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.17"
msgid "“karohi dāni te, āvuso, cīvaran”ti."
msgstr "“Why don’t you make a robe for yourself?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.18"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "And he told them what had happened."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_560
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.19"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.20"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.21"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ dassatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can a monk give robe-cloth to a nun?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.22"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ adāsī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.23"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.24"
msgid "“Ñātikā te, bhikkhu, aññātikā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is she a relative of yours?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.25"
msgid "“Aññātikā, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.283
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.26"
msgid "“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātikāya na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā santaṃ vā asantaṃ vā."
msgstr "“Foolish man, a man and a woman who are not related don’t know what’s appropriate and what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s right and what’s wrong."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.27"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ dassasi."
msgstr "And still you gave robe-cloth to an unrelated nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.28"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.29"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_561
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.30"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ dadeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk gives robe-cloth to an unrelated nun, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_562
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:1.31"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. VAR: pārivattakaṃ → pārivaṭṭakaṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. REF: sc6, pts-vp-pli4.60, pts-cs-bu-pc25.2, ms2V_563,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā bhikkhunīnaṃ pārivattakaṃ cīvaraṃ na denti."
msgstr "Once this had happened, monks did not even give robe-cloth to nuns in exchange, being afraid of wrongdoing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.2"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The nuns complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.3"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma ayyā amhākaṃ pārivattakaṃ cīvaraṃ na dassantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can they not give us robe-cloth in exchange?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_564
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.4"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those nuns"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.5"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.7"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ pārivattakaṃ dātuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, if it is part of an exchange, I allow you to give things to five groups of people:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.8"
msgid "Bhikkhussa, bhikkhuniyā, sikkhamānāya, sāmaṇerassa, sāmaṇeriyā—"
msgstr "monks, nuns, trainee nuns, novice monks, and novice nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.9"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imesaṃ pañcannaṃ pārivattakaṃ dātuṃ."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.10"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.10a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p>_Cīvara_ means both a finished robe and any cloth that can be used to make a robe. Thus I vary my translation depending on the context.<span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_565
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:2.11"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ dadeyya, aññatra pārivattakā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk gives robe-cloth to an unrelated nun, unless it is an exchange, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, pts-cs-bu-pc25.3.1, ms2V_566
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_567
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.6"
msgid "Aññātikā nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.7"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddhā."
msgstr "anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, pts-vp-en.2.284, ms2V_568
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.8"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "A nun:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.9"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "she has been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_569,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.10"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Robe-cloth:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
# NOTE: The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see [](Mv.8.3.1).
# NOTE: This means not smaller than 8 by 4 standard (_sugata_) finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see [](Kkh.94.4) and BMC I, pp.565-566. 
#. VAR: vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ → vikap­pa­nupaga­pacchi­maṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.11"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr "one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_570
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.12"
msgid "Aññatra pārivattakāti"
msgstr "Unless it is an exchange:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.1.13"
msgid "ṭhapetvā pārivattakaṃ deti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "except if it is an exchange."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc14, pts-cs-bu-pc25.3.2, ms2V_571
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.2.1"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī cīvaraṃ deti, aññatra pārivattakā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gives her robe-cloth, unless it is an exchange, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.2.2"
msgid "Aññātikāya vematiko cīvaraṃ deti, aññatra pārivattakā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated, but he is unsure if she is, and he gives her robe-cloth, unless it is an exchange, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.2.3"
msgid "Aññātikāya ñātikasaññī cīvaraṃ deti, aññatra pārivattakā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated, but he perceives her as related, and he gives her robe-cloth, unless it is an exchange, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_572
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.2.4"
msgid "Ekato upasampannāya cīvaraṃ deti, aññatra pārivattakā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he gives robe-cloth to a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, unless it is an exchange, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.2.5"
msgid "Ñātikāya aññātikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is related, but he perceives her as unrelated, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.2.6"
msgid "Ñātikāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is related, but he is unsure if she is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.2.7"
msgid "Ñātikāya ñātikasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If she is related and he perceives her as related, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc16, pts-cs-bu-pc25.3.3, ms2V_573
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.2"
msgid "ñātikāya,"
msgstr "if she is related;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.3"
msgid "pārivattakaṃ parittena vā vipulaṃ, vipulena vā parittaṃ,"
msgstr "if much is exchanged with little or little is exchanged with much;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.4"
msgid "bhikkhunī vissāsaṃ gaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if the nun takes it on trust;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.5"
msgid "tāvakālikaṃ gaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if she borrows it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.6"
msgid "cīvaraṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ deti,"
msgstr "if he gives any requisite apart from robe-cloth;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.7"
msgid "sikkhamānāya,"
msgstr "if it is a trainee nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.8"
msgid "sāmaṇeriyā,"
msgstr "if it is a novice nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.9"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.10"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc17, ms2V_574
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc25:3.3.11"
msgid "Cīvaradānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr "The fifth rule, the training rule on giving robe-cloth, is finished."
